Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? BC SRC Provincial Assistant (Contract) Remote , BC Description The BC Summer Reading Club (BC SRC) is a free literacy program designed to engage children with a focus on ages 5-14. The program reaches more than 173,000 children and their families in over 200 BC communities. The BC Library Association is seeking a Provincial Assistant, BC SRC, to help support this important program. If you're passionate about SRC and children's library services, have great attention to detail, enjoy making creative content, and work well with minimal supervision in a collaborative team environment, we'd love to hear from you! Position Summary
The Provincial Assistant, BC SRC, provides leadership and coordination for the annual BC Summer Reading Club. Working under the supervision of the Provincial Coordinator, BC SRC and with limited coordination with the Core Committee, creative team, and BC libraries, the Assistant helps with communications, weekly website updates, and content creation for bcsrc.ca. The Assistant reports to the Provincial Coordinator, BC SRC. Contract Term &amp; Schedule: This is a contract position with work expected to begin September 2023 and last until the end of August 2024. Approximately 200 to 250 hours of work with a flexible schedule, the possibility of extension, and additional hours with approval from the BCLA Executive Director. Location: This is a distributed work contract. The successful candidate will provide their own equipment, home office and supplies, including a reliable high speed internet connection, and will supply and maintain their own computer. BCLA will provide access to an Office 365 account and all required software for the term of the contract. Work Performed Helps the Coordinator lead the Core Committee in planning themes and overall materials design for the SRC Work with the Coordinator to guide the Core Committee in the selection of each year’s artist Oversee the Core Committee in creating the annual manual Oversee and coordinate the ordering and distribution of Core Materials Work with the Coordinator to communicate updates, timelines, news to BC libraries, including articles for YAACing and blog posts for the SRC staff site and social media accounts Create and execute content for bcsrc.ca, including weekly activities and contests for BC SRC participants Set up weekly website updates during the duration of BC Summer Reading Club (approximately 7 weeks) including weekly contest entries, content uploads, and more Creation of promotional content for BC SRC for social media channels (Instagram, Twitter) with the guidance of the Provincial Coordinator Send and reply to enquiries from members of the public and other general communication related to BC SRC via email, social media Manage online records and files Document and maintain aspects of the role for an “Assistant’s Manual” Coordinate the SRC Community Story Award (submissions, selection, presentation) Work with the Core Committee in planning SRC promotion at the Conference booth display Provide Provincial Coordinator with updates on progress of tasks And potential additional administrative tasks related to BC SRC Required Skills/Experience Excellent oral and written communication skills Excellent organization and multi-tasking Knowledge of public libraries and children’s services (with an emphasis on programming and readers’ advisory) Strong collaboration skills Experience working in public libraries and with the SRC program Creativity and content creation experience is an asset Knowledge and experience working with Office 365, WordPress, social media platforms, video conferencing, online project management tools, Canva, and other design related tools Ability to work in a distributed organization with little or no direct supervision Commitment to accessibility, anti-racism and inclusivity. How to apply
Please email your resume and cover letter, as a single pdf format document, to the BCLA Office by midnight on August 29, 2023 with the subject line: Provincial Assistant application. Questions of clarification can be submitted to the BCLA Office. Should you require any accommodations at any point during the application and hiring process, please contact the BCLA Office. Our Selection Process We will review all applications starting August 30. We thank all candidates for their interest, but only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. We expect to conduct interviews via Zoom from September 11-17. Interview questions will be provided to each candidate 48 hours before their interview. All candidates will be asked the same questions and answers will evaluated against a rubric. We will check references for the highest rated 1-3 candidates the following week and communicate our decision by September 25. Our decision will be communicated to everyone who was interviewed before any public announcements are made. If our process is delayed at any stage, we will email candidates with an updated timeline. Compensation $28/hour (plus GST if applicable) Closes: 29 August, 2023 British Columbia Library Association Remote , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
