Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Assistant Chief Librarian Nelson , BC Description Position Summary: The Nelson Public Library is seeking a progressive and dynamic Assistant Chief Librarian with a strong community focus and excellent management skills. Reporting to the Chief Librarian, the Assistant Chief Librarian is responsible for promoting a welcoming and inviting library environment and delivering a library service that meets the strategic direction of the Library. The position works closely with the Chief Librarian in the overall administration and day-to-day operations of the library and serves as Acting Chief in the Chief’s absence. Key reports to this position include Department Coordinators and Library Assistants. This position leads the oversight of technology programming and innovation for the Library. It also assists the Chief Librarian with strategic planning, service assessment, community relations and staff development. Nelson Public Library’s newly adopted value-based Strategic Framework was developed to enable Library staff and board to root decision-making in values and to provide a roadmap for ongoing priorities. EDI, Climate and Indigenization were used as an overarching lens to support the development of the framework. Setting: Located within the traditional land of the Sinixt, Ktunaxa and Sylix peoples, the Nelson Public Library serves a population of approx. 19,000 that encompasses the City of Nelson and Areas F, H &amp; E of the Regional District of the Central Kootenays. We are grateful for the opportunity to work on this land. Nelson is traditionally known for its beautiful setting, a vast array of recreational activities, pristine parks and vibrant downtown. It is a year-round playground for outdoor enthusiasts and those who love the arts, culture and small-town feel, with big-city amenities like high-quality schools, post-secondary institutions, regional health care and a competitive cost of living. Primary Duties and Responsibilities: Serves as the lead in the development of the Library’s digital strategy including the Tech Hub, public and staff training and programming. Ensuring digital services meet the needs of staff and people in the community.Providing advice, assistance and recommendations to the Chief Librarian on a range of library matters including strategic planning, assessment and fund development (grants &amp; fundraising).Assisting with hiring, directing, leading and evaluating performance of staff and ensuring appropriate staff development. Participates in employee and labour relations matters.Champions the work of staff members by fostering open communication, providing leadership and motivation, assessing their strengths and development needs, and encouraging and empowering them to achieve.Continually modeling and reinforcing a collaborative and collegial team approach to library operations. Encourages creativity, and innovation.Nurture existing community relationships and partnerships, develop new ones, to identify and address the evolving needs of the community.Supports the Chief Librarian in the development and monitoring of financial budgets.Acts as the Chief Librarian in their absence.Assists with special initiatives as required. Qualifications: Master’s Degree in Library Science from an accredited Library school;Three to five years of recent relevant experience in a senior leadership role, or an equivalent combination of education and experience;The ideal candidate has a background in public library services, strong leadership and communication skills, a commitment to equity, diversity, and inclusion and community-based service development. How to apply: Find a full description of the position role, including required qualifications and experience and how to apply at nelson.ca/jobs We thank all applicants for their interest in Nelson Public Library. We encourage you to apply even if you do not have all the qualifications we list here. Only those selected for an interview will be contacted. NPL believes that diversifying our staff will make our organization better and more reflective of the community we serve. We encourage people of all genders, ages, ethnicities, cultures, abilities, sexual orientations, and life experiences to apply Compensation $71,076 - $78,557 Closes: 25 August, 2023 Nelson Public Library Nelson , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
