ies and festivals Forges partnerships with a dynamic and diverse community to enhance the library’s visibility and usage Teaches digital and information literacy in their daily interactions with the public or in group settings, helping patrons develop skills required to locate, evaluate and use resources effectively Promotes collections by preparing bibliographies, indexes, reading lists, guides and other finding aids Develops and maintains the library’s adult collections through weeding and selection of new material with an emphasis on maintenance and development of the reference, local history and genealogy collections Addresses reference desk inquiries, takes the lead in providing local history information to community members and responds to inquiries from around the world Organizes/provides direction for the development of displays in the library or in the community to promote library Participates in social media and online presence (Facebook, Event Brite, You Tube, etc.) Participates in public, community and media relations Compiles statistics on program attendance and prepares reports Other duties as requiredQualifications Master’s degree in Library and/or information sciences from an ALA accredited program or equivalent Two years’ experience working in a public library Strong ability to build relationships and engage with the community: develop and maintain partnerships, and professionally interact with partners Proven ability to teach, facilitate, role model, mentor and act as a resource. Strong programming, communication and presentation skills Demonstrated ability to exercise initiative, tact, leadership and independent judgment. Strong time-management skills; demonstrated ability to manage multiple projects with minimal supervision Demonstrated commitment to providing exceptional customer service Knowledge of best practices and current trends in library services and programs for adults Current knowledge of automated library environments, office software and web applications Fluency in both official languages preferred (English and French) Access to a vehicle with a ‘G’ license Current and Clear Criminal Record Check with Vulnerable Sector Screen requiredHow to ApplyPlease submit your application to the Human Resources Department by 4:00 pm on the closing date of August 15, 2023.Via Email: human_resources@timmins.caThe City of Timmins is committed to providing a safe and supportive workplace where diversity, equity and inclusion are at the core of how we conduct business. As part of this commitment, we will ensure that persons with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodations throughout the recruitment and selection process, in accordance with the Accessibility for Ontarians with Disabilities Act and the Ontario Human Rights Code. Personal information provided is collected under the authority of The Municipal Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act. We thank all applicants for their interest; however, only candidates under consideration will be contacted.www.timmins.cawww.movetotimmins.ca(705) 264-1331 Compensation $28.66 - $37.08/hour (2023) Closes: 15 August, 2023 CIty of Timmins Timmins , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
